<title>USA: Harmon Industries places $15 mln debt.</title>
<headline>Harmon Industries places $15 mln debt.</headline>
<dateline>BLUE SPRINGS, Mo. 1997-01-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Harmon Industries Inc, a supplier of railroad signal and train control equipment, said Monday it completed $15 million in private placement of senior unsecured notes with CIGNA Investments Inc.</p>
<p>The notes, due in 2007, have a 10-year maturity and an average life of seven years. They were priced to yield 6.87 precent.</p>
<p>Harmon said it will use the proceeds to provide working capital and to finance acquisition plans.</p>
